<normalizedToken id="D363169A16857B54E85D3F5C673C3A71" originalValue="Harin’Hala">Harin'Hala</normalizedToken>
, Malaise trap, in low altitude rainforest, elev. 825 m, MA-29-11&quot; (1 ♂, CAS).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="13482317BC8D287C7040BE9E35ECEB17" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph id="A8F1F8815D09CC39E3EADB74004D8730" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B532561247625AD7CF2E26E75E2516DB" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="72A1056EA1F41CBE4B0CA9CEF9107AC7" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="male">
<paragraph id="98877E20F67D2B398A0E0A345C7BB5C5" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Male</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B9988F9D7C32F76FB82EA4752723A593" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
(
<figureCitation id="4A19D110362965F4444684BAA72DAFE5" captionStart="Figures 29–30" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 29 - 30. Orthogonalys parahova, holotype male. 29 Dorsolateral view. 30 Mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11365" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Length, 10.0 -11.0 mm. Antenna black; antennomeres 11 at apex, 12-15, and base of 16 white. Head white with vertex and upper frons black, black extending to dorsal margins of eyes and medially to near antennal sockets (
<figureCitation id="3A30F17C95A66C2149E62B13B787B97E" captionStart="Figures 31–34" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 31 - 34. Orthogonalys parahova, holotype male. 31 Head, front view. 32 Head, dorsal view. 33 Apex of abdomen and male genitalia, lateral view. 34, Mandibles." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11366" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 31, 32</figureCitation>
); clypeus white. Mesosoma orange with posterior lateral angles of pronotum white and metascutellum yellow; pleura and sterna lighter orange than dorsum. Legs orange with hind tibia and tarsus black. Wings hyaline with veins and stigma black. Metasoma with tergite 1 mostly black, tergites 2-4 orange, tergite 5 mostly black, and tergites 6 and 7 white, narrow lateral edges of tergites white and sternites mostly white; genitalia with gonostipes brown and paramere white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2763FC0DF02CD7910CAD51AC197DEC61" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Antenna with 28-29 antennomeres. Head from above slightly emarginated behind; head behind eyes about 0.8
<normalizedToken id="AB744C589E63A4A906AD17AE40B88A8C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye length (
<figureCitation id="C68785BF8149CB7AB88EA1D731C1A966" captionStart="Figures 31–34" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 31 - 34. Orthogonalys parahova, holotype male. 31 Head, front view. 32 Head, dorsal view. 33 Apex of abdomen and male genitalia, lateral view. 34, Mandibles." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11366" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Anterior width of mesoscutellum about 1.2
<normalizedToken id="685908D3E8776955F716317779ACF28E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
medial length; shallow, median longitudinal groove on posterior half (
<figureCitation id="4DA682A3E0908AC2E4A161DA044C80BD" captionStart="Figures 31–34" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 31 - 34. Orthogonalys parahova, holotype male. 31 Head, front view. 32 Head, dorsal view. 33 Apex of abdomen and male genitalia, lateral view. 34, Mandibles." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11366" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Metascutellum 2
<normalizedToken id="4467E8551F3F8F3F358DCD84921B0796" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long. Mesonotum shiny with closely set punctures, mostly separated by shiny interspaces 1 - 2
<normalizedToken id="453F7E9EA4E6FBDA9407878E8B1D05F2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
puncture diameters. Propodeum with irregular transverse carinae at center, more reticulate on sides (
<figureCitation id="5391326ECC3458FBA85FAACC86D53424" captionStart="Figures 31–34" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 31 - 34. Orthogonalys parahova, holotype male. 31 Head, front view. 32 Head, dorsal view. 33 Apex of abdomen and male genitalia, lateral view. 34, Mandibles." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11366" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Paramere of male genitalia about 1.8
<normalizedToken id="928CBEC99EEA8C917A9592702B84F614" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, broadly rounded at apex (
<figureCitation id="D1312D1CE92E97BE6D74A2EDE5C294E4" captionStart="Figures 31–34" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 31 - 34. Orthogonalys parahova, holotype male. 31 Head, front view. 32 Head, dorsal view. 33 Apex of abdomen and male genitalia, lateral view. 34, Mandibles." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11366" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
), subequal in length to gonostipes (as in 
<figureCitation id="AECC19CDA1EDC8F30A7A8E3823D386CE" captionStart="Figures 23–28" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 23 - 28. Orthogonalys maculata, male. 23 Mesosoma, dorsal view. 24 Head, front view. 25 Head, dorsal view. 26 Antenna. 27 Apex of abdomen and genitalia, lateral view. 28 Genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11364" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
